Biological investigations in alcohol research. The biological mechanisms examined in this paper cover only a small portion of those that may be involved in the pathogenesis of alcoholism. Certain areas on which a great deal of work has already been done have been entirely omitted. Among these are studies on brain acetylcholine and gamma-aminobutyric acid metabolism in alcohol-related conditions the effect of alcohol on brain proteins and nucleotides and the relationship of changes in these to the development of tolerance and physical dependence